  "event_preview": "Seekonk Speedway is a 0.333-mile (0.536 km) asphalt oval in Seekonk, Massachusetts — known as the Cement Palace, though the racing surface is asphalt — a tight, technical third-mile that rewards precise line selection and throttle application above raw horsepower. The Modified Tour has competed here since 2023 following a long absence, and the track's partially repaved corners have made it one of the most technically demanding venues on the calendar.\n\nMatt Hirschman has won every Modified Tour event at Seekonk since the series' return in 2023 — three consecutive victories — and has led 65 percent of the laps run in those events while setting fast time in qualifying for each race. Stephen Kopcik, winner of the two most recent Tour events at Martinsville and Thompson, is the most credible threat, having finished second at Seekonk last year before a last-lap crash ended multiple contenders' nights. Doug Coby makes his second start of the year in the No. 28 for Jett Motorsports, the six-time series champion a two-time winner at this venue, while four-time champion Justin Bonsignore — who had previously planned to skip this event — is entered for Ken Massa Motorsports.\n\nThe Whelen Modified Tour has competed at Seekonk in its current return era only since 2023, meaning the all-time series qualifying and race lap records at this venue are those set across the three most recent runnings — the fastest qualifying lap belonging to Hirschman from the 2025 edition.",
